1️⃣ Queue Operations (FIFO)
🔹 Concept

Queue follows FIFO → First In, First Out.

🧠 Python Code (4 lines)
q=[]
q.append(10); q.append(20)
print(q.pop(0))
print(q)

🖥️ Output
10
[20]

📖 Explanation

append() → Insert at rear (enqueue)

pop(0) → Remove from front (dequeue)

10 entered first → removed first

⏱️ Interview Insight

Time Complexity:

Enqueue → O(1)

Dequeue (list) → O(n)

In interviews, better to use collections.deque for O(1).

🎤 Interview Explanation

“Queue operates on FIFO principle where insertion happens at rear and deletion at front.”

2️⃣ Circular Queue Concept
🔹 Concept

In circular queue:

After reaching end, queue wraps around to front.

Prevents unused empty space.

🧠 Python Code (6 lines)
n=3; q=[None]*n; f=r=0
q[r]=10; r=(r+1)%n
q[r]=20; r=(r+1)%n
print(q)

🖥️ Output
[10, 20, None]

📖 Explanation

% n makes index wrap around.

Used in:

Buffers

Scheduling

OS processes

⏱️ Interview Insight

Efficient memory usage

Avoids shifting elements

🎤 Interview Explanation

“Circular queue uses modulo operation to reuse empty spaces efficiently.”

🎤 FAANG Interview Round (Professional Answers)

Q1. Difference between Stack and Queue?
A: Stack is LIFO, Queue is FIFO.

Q2. Why not use list for queue in real interviews?
A: Because pop(0) is O(n). deque is better.

Q3. Where are queues used?
A: BFS, scheduling, printer queue, CPU scheduling.

Q4. What is advantage of circular queue?
A: Better space utilization.

